Popular stand-up comedian, Julius Agwu has announced his comedy show, ‘Crack Ya Ribs’ will be returning after a long halt Agwu, in an interview with Hip TV, said the show will make a comeback this Easter in Kaduna. The comedian empathised with victims of the Abuja-Kaduna train attack of March 28 where terrorists bombed the train, killed eight passengers on board and kidnapped unspecified number of others. He stated he had plans to cancel the show but agreed to go on with it after the organisers insisted. “’Crack Ya Ribs’ has been on for a long time. As a matter of fact were supposed to celebrate the 15 years, last year in London but some things happened but it is fine. So ‘Crack Ya Ribs’ is taking place in Kaduna State. *As a matter of fact, when some things happened in Kaduna, I wanted the move the show but they said, ‘no’ that I should come and do it; that it’s fine.   Osinachi’s husband should be imprisoned – Uche…     Ugandan filmmaker eyes new Africa narrative after Disney…     Why I flaunt my pregnancy – Rihanna   “So, I just want to say that all the people that were involved in the railway train bombing should take heart. They should stay strong. So, that’s why I’m doing this show just to let them know that in as much as they lost lives, God is with.” Reacting, social media users expressed worry over his decision to carry on with the show. abolore_twins said: “Did u just say Kaduna hmmmm , i hope the money been paid to come for this show will be enough to settle bandit.” _abdul__jnr wrote: “I no get money for ransom.” crazytushae stated: “Ishi a digi nma ( your head no correct ) you should have added featuring Bandits , headsmen , kidnappers and some other comedians way get odieshi.” angelaucheeri asked: “Why kaduna?”